1
00:01:18,262 --> 00:01:19,073
Hello Albert.

2
00:01:19,097 --> 00:01:21,905
What's going on here?

3
00:01:21,929 --> 00:01:23,363
Chinese wedding?

4
00:01:23,387 --> 00:01:24,971
No, funeral.

5
00:01:27,137 --> 00:01:29,488
Is somebody dead?

6
00:01:29,512 --> 00:01:31,072
I hope so.

7
00:01:31,096 --> 00:01:32,221
They're gonna bury him.

8
00:01:33,179 --> 00:01:35,137
Ooh, who?

9
00:01:35,179 --> 00:01:36,804
Dr. Fu Manchu.

10
00:01:36,846 --> 00:01:39,238
Haven't you ever read about him?

11
00:01:51,762 --> 00:01:53,863
Do you feel equal to going in?

12
00:01:53,887 --> 00:01:55,863
No, no Inspector Smith.

13
00:01:55,887 --> 00:01:57,596
It's still so horrible to me.

14
00:01:58,762 --> 00:02:00,447
I'll take Lia for a little drive

15
00:02:00,471 --> 00:02:02,030
and we'll pick you up later.

16
00:02:02,054 --> 00:02:03,346
All right Dr. Betreace.

17
00:02:07,804 --> 00:02:09,197
Oh, I say, Inspector.

18
00:02:09,221 --> 00:02:10,697
Oh, hello Camden.

19
00:02:10,721 --> 00:02:12,572
Are you covering this for your paper?

20
00:02:12,596 --> 00:02:15,322
Yes, there are several
details I wish to clear out.

21
00:02:15,346 --> 00:02:16,863
Well, I'll be glad to help you

22
00:02:16,887 --> 00:02:18,488
if you'll come inside and wait for me

23
00:02:18,512 --> 00:02:20,488
while I officially attend the service.

24
00:02:20,512 --> 00:02:21,721
Thanks very much.

25
00:03:57,929 --> 00:03:59,887
- Let's sit down here.
- Oh, thanks.

26
00:04:03,971 --> 00:04:08,238
Can you tell me how many men
Fu Manchu actually murdered?

27
00:04:08,262 --> 00:04:10,155
I'm afraid we'll never know,

28
00:04:10,179 --> 00:04:11,804
he was too clever in his methods.

29
00:04:13,012 --> 00:04:15,197
Look here, Camden, can't
you persuade your paper

30
00:04:15,221 --> 00:04:17,947
to soften that part of the story?

31
00:04:17,971 --> 00:04:21,822
Before Fu Manchu went insane,
he was a magnificent scientist

32
00:04:21,846 --> 00:04:22,823
working for mankind.

33
00:04:22,847 --> 00:04:26,155
And not only that,
during the boxer rioting

34
00:04:26,179 --> 00:04:28,530
he was the best friend the
White man had in China.

35
00:04:28,554 --> 00:04:32,030
And when the Chinese rebel
attacked the British delegation

36
00:04:32,054 --> 00:04:35,447
Eltham, one of the missionaries
sent his little girl

37
00:04:35,471 --> 00:04:36,762
to Fu for safety.

38
00:04:37,637 --> 00:04:39,822
But some of the Chinese snipers

39
00:04:39,846 --> 00:04:43,197
used Fu's garden wall for protection.

40
00:04:43,221 --> 00:04:45,863
The White troops were obliged to fire

41
00:04:45,887 --> 00:04:50,780
and Fu Manchu's wife and
little son whom he adored

42
00:04:50,804 --> 00:04:52,905
were killed before his eyes.

43
00:04:52,929 --> 00:04:54,280
Is that why he went insane?

44
00:04:54,304 --> 00:04:55,137
Yes.

45
00:04:55,179 --> 00:04:57,280
And in the mistaken belief
that his White friends

46
00:04:57,304 --> 00:04:59,822
had intentionally fired on his house,

47
00:04:59,846 --> 00:05:02,447
he swore to his gods
that he'd wiped them out

48
00:05:02,471 --> 00:05:04,488
to the third generation.

49
00:05:04,512 --> 00:05:06,697
And that he would use the child,

50
00:05:06,721 --> 00:05:08,988
Lia Eltham in his vengeance.

51
00:05:09,012 --> 00:05:11,947
The next 20 years, Fu spent murdering

52
00:05:11,971 --> 00:05:15,554
the surviving officers
of the boxer rioting

53
00:05:16,721 --> 00:05:19,554
in Russia, Germany and France.

54
00:05:23,846 --> 00:05:28,780
And just before death, Fu
sent to each of his victims

55
00:05:28,804 --> 00:05:30,221
this blood-stained dragon.

56
00:05:32,137 --> 00:05:34,304
The stain represents his wife's blood.

57
00:05:35,721 --> 00:05:38,530
For every officer he murdered,

58
00:05:38,554 --> 00:05:41,863
He re gilded a scale that
had been covered with blood.

59
00:05:41,887 --> 00:05:43,322
Ah, there's one left.

60
00:05:43,346 --> 00:05:46,387
Yes, he meant to kill
young Petrie for that scale.

61
00:05:47,846 --> 00:05:50,197
He brought the girl Lia into the plot,

62
00:05:50,221 --> 00:05:52,947
all entirely innocently upon her father

63
00:05:52,971 --> 00:05:54,721
and used her to lure the boy.

64
00:05:55,637 --> 00:05:58,280
And one time he actually
had them both prisoners

65
00:05:58,304 --> 00:05:59,198
in Limehouse.

66
00:05:59,222 --> 00:06:02,613
Ah, that was when you made
your famous capture, wasn't it?

67
00:06:02,637 --> 00:06:05,405
I'm afraid death made the capture.

68
00:06:05,429 --> 00:06:09,113
He took some Oriental poison he concocted

69
00:06:09,137 --> 00:06:10,137
just as we got him.

70
00:06:12,387 --> 00:06:13,947
A delightful chap.

71
00:06:13,971 --> 00:06:16,387
Inspector, why are you here today?

72
00:06:17,929 --> 00:06:19,863
To see the coffin sealed

73
00:06:19,887 --> 00:06:24,613
and also to pay my respects
to a truly great man.

74
00:07:28,429 --> 00:07:30,863
Just one more thing, Inspector.

75
00:07:30,887 --> 00:07:33,929
What's happened to young
Petrie and the girl?

76
00:07:35,846 --> 00:07:37,363
They've been through a horrible ordeal,

77
00:07:37,387 --> 00:07:41,221
but they're young and very much in love.

78
00:07:42,179 --> 00:07:43,197
As a matter of fact,

79
00:07:43,221 --> 00:07:46,846
I've got my eye on a wedding present.

80
00:08:25,679 --> 00:08:29,030
As nice a funeral as I could wish for.

81
00:08:29,054 --> 00:08:30,054
Yes Master.

82
00:08:30,846 --> 00:08:35,012
Do not look so serious,
stupid one.

83
00:08:35,887 --> 00:08:40,054
This wax on my face makes
it difficult to laugh.

84
00:08:44,387 --> 00:08:48,238
And now Chang, we have work to do.

85
00:08:48,262 --> 00:08:52,179
We must not tolerate
interference from anyone.

86
00:09:03,262 --> 00:09:07,280
Gods of my ancestors, help me to keep

87
00:09:07,304 --> 00:09:09,762
my solemn promise to you.

88
00:09:10,887 --> 00:09:13,613
Only one life more.

89
00:09:13,637 --> 00:09:16,447
Let the blood of Jack Petrie

90
00:09:16,471 --> 00:09:20,304
wipe this stain from the house of Fu.

91
00:09:27,554 --> 00:09:30,512
Do you hear that?

92
00:09:30,554 --> 00:09:32,637
The organist is practicing
the wedding march

93
00:09:32,679 --> 00:09:33,679
in the chapel.

94
00:09:35,679 --> 00:09:37,572
Wasn't it nice of Aunt
Agatha and Aunt Helen

95
00:09:37,596 --> 00:09:39,197
to have the wedding here?

96
00:09:39,221 --> 00:09:40,031
Yes.

97
00:09:40,055 --> 00:09:43,471
You know my great grandfather
was married in that chapel.

98
00:09:44,471 --> 00:09:47,221
In a few more hours we'll be married.

99
00:09:48,304 --> 00:09:51,072
Nancy was telling
me, the Lohengrin March

100
00:09:51,096 --> 00:09:52,863
always comes first.

101
00:09:55,179 --> 00:09:57,655
Slowly and solemnly up
to the altar like that.

102
00:09:57,679 --> 00:09:58,738
And then.

103
00:10:02,471 --> 00:10:05,863
Back down the isle in
triumph in the spirit of,

104
00:10:05,887 --> 00:10:07,238
I've got my man.

105
00:10:07,262 --> 00:10:09,572
Agatha.

106
00:10:09,596 --> 00:10:11,262
Oh, there you are.

107
00:10:14,762 --> 00:10:15,762
Hello.

108
00:10:17,929 --> 00:10:20,072
I don't know how we'll
ever be able to thank you

109
00:10:20,096 --> 00:10:23,072
and Aunt Helen for all
you're doing for us.

110
00:10:23,096 --> 00:10:26,572
My dear, you've already
paid us a thousandfold.

111
00:10:26,596 --> 00:10:28,197
Indeed you have.

112
00:10:28,221 --> 00:10:32,322
Don't you realize the thrill
two maiden ladies feel

113
00:10:32,346 --> 00:10:34,655
having a wedding in their own house.

114
00:10:34,679 --> 00:10:36,155
Speak for yourself, my dear.

115
00:10:36,179 --> 00:10:38,322
I get no thrill at all out of sentiment.

116
00:10:38,346 --> 00:10:41,238
Oh, don't put on your
Amazon mood Agatha.

117
00:10:46,554 --> 00:10:49,637
- Look where you're going.
- I can't.

118
00:10:52,346 --> 00:10:54,697
Oh, get along, get it.

119
00:10:54,721 --> 00:10:55,721
Get along.

120
00:10:56,554 --> 00:10:59,762
The old spirit is willing,
but the flesh is weak.

121
00:11:00,971 --> 00:11:03,072
What's the matter with you, Sylvester?

122
00:11:03,096 --> 00:11:04,988
You're quaking like a jelly.

123
00:11:05,012 --> 00:11:06,655
I can't help you, lady Agatha.

124
00:11:06,679 --> 00:11:09,113
Ever since Fu Manchu came into my life,

125
00:11:09,137 --> 00:11:12,113
I've been nothing but a nervous wreck.

126
00:11:12,137 --> 00:11:15,488
I've imbibed eight strong
cups of tea since breakfast,

127
00:11:15,512 --> 00:11:16,822
but nothing seems to help.

128
00:11:16,846 --> 00:11:18,363
Well, there's nothing
to be nervous about now.

129
00:11:18,387 --> 00:11:20,262
Fu Manchu is dead, isn't he?

130
00:11:21,179 --> 00:11:22,304
So they tell me.

131
00:11:24,054 --> 00:11:27,262
Whoa, my soul and body.

132
00:11:29,721 --> 00:11:32,572
Wait, don't do it, I beg of you.

133
00:11:32,596 --> 00:11:34,405
What's the matter now?

134
00:11:34,429 --> 00:11:37,822
There's nothing in the world
so sure to bring bad luck

135
00:11:37,846 --> 00:11:41,280
as the groom kissing the
bride before the wedding.

136
00:11:41,304 --> 00:11:42,697
Rubbish.

137
00:11:42,721 --> 00:11:44,197
If they didn't kiss before the wedding,

138
00:11:44,221 --> 00:11:45,679
there'd never be any wedding.

139
00:11:46,596 --> 00:11:49,155
Now run along you to
uncover the marriage service

140
00:11:49,179 --> 00:11:50,197
in the prayer book.

141
00:11:50,221 --> 00:11:52,387
You don't know a word
of it, either of you.

142
00:11:53,887 --> 00:11:55,512
I'll take care of him.

143
00:11:56,429 --> 00:11:58,054
Oh, please don't.

144
00:11:59,262 --> 00:12:00,846
Leave them alone.

145
00:12:16,762 --> 00:12:19,221
To love and to cherish
until death us do part.

146
00:12:27,429 --> 00:12:28,887
We're going to be so happy.

147
00:12:33,096 --> 00:12:34,262
What was that?

148
00:12:36,512 --> 00:12:38,471
That was only an aeroplane shadow.

149
00:12:44,387 --> 00:12:45,387
Lia?

150
00:12:48,012 --> 00:12:52,947
I feel just the way I used
to when Dr. Fu was alive

151
00:12:52,971 --> 00:12:54,363
and near.

152
00:12:54,387 --> 00:12:55,387
Oh no.

153
00:13:15,429 --> 00:13:18,596
Is everything prepared
as I have ordered?

154
00:13:20,096 --> 00:13:25,096
Is the camouflage
arranged for our airplane?

155
00:13:25,804 --> 00:13:27,780
I did as you ordered, Master.

156
00:13:27,804 --> 00:13:30,905
And the wedding of Dr. Petrie,

157
00:13:30,929 --> 00:13:34,197
it takes place today.

158
00:13:34,221 --> 00:13:37,030
Yes, today, honorable one.

159
00:13:37,054 --> 00:13:38,387
Good.

160
00:13:38,429 --> 00:13:42,363
Although they have not seen
fit to send me an invitation,

161
00:13:42,387 --> 00:13:46,072
I shall be nevertheless an interested,

162
00:13:46,096 --> 00:13:49,304
though invisible, guest.

163
00:13:52,804 --> 00:13:53,614
Wow, you are lovely.

164
00:13:53,638 --> 00:13:55,947
Come and have a look at
yourself in the large mirror.

165
00:13:55,971 --> 00:13:57,738
Just lovely.

166
00:13:57,762 --> 00:14:01,155
That gown is beautiful and
you're going to be so happy,

167
00:14:01,179 --> 00:14:02,114
I know.

168
00:14:02,138 --> 00:14:04,363
Oh, I love weddings, dear.

169
00:14:04,387 --> 00:14:06,072
Oh, I love those pearls.

170
00:14:06,096 --> 00:14:07,137
Pins, where are my pins?

171
00:14:09,804 --> 00:14:12,738
Fai Lu, I'm going to
throw the wedding bouquet

172
00:14:12,762 --> 00:14:14,863
straight at you, see that you catch it.

173
00:14:14,887 --> 00:14:15,887
I'll catch.

174
00:14:22,679 --> 00:14:24,447
Look how dark it's getting.

175
00:14:24,471 --> 00:14:26,322
There must be a storm coming.

176
00:14:26,346 --> 00:14:29,762
Yes, I think we should have some light.

177
00:14:41,887 --> 00:14:46,846
There's so much to remember
and exactly as much to forget.

178
00:14:48,221 --> 00:14:51,197
Ring, right hand, left hand, pass over.

179
00:14:51,221 --> 00:14:53,655
Ring, right hand, left hand, pass over.

180
00:14:53,679 --> 00:14:56,113
Ring, right hand, left hand, pass over.

181
00:14:56,137 --> 00:14:57,697
Ring, right hand, left hand, pass over.

182
00:15:00,971 --> 00:15:03,780
Stop, I dread you stop.

183
00:15:03,804 --> 00:15:05,238
Stop what?

184
00:15:05,262 --> 00:15:08,947
That whistling, it's bad luck.

185
00:15:08,971 --> 00:15:09,971
All right.

186
00:15:15,637 --> 00:15:16,637
Don't!

187
00:15:17,679 --> 00:15:19,947
It's worse luck to sing than to whistle.

188
00:15:21,262 --> 00:15:22,863
So tell me, Sylvester,

189
00:15:22,887 --> 00:15:25,447
is it bad like to strangle your best man?

190
00:15:25,471 --> 00:15:26,697
I don't think so.

191
00:15:26,721 --> 00:15:27,822
No, excellent.

192
00:15:29,596 --> 00:15:31,429
Let go, leave me alone.

193
00:15:32,971 --> 00:15:34,137
I'm so nervous now.

194
00:15:39,762 --> 00:15:42,030
Oh, you're going to take that long trip

195
00:15:42,054 --> 00:15:43,822
just to give me away.

196
00:15:43,846 --> 00:15:45,947
You are a darling to ask me.

197
00:15:45,971 --> 00:15:48,655
You know, I feel as
though you belong to me.

198
00:15:48,679 --> 00:15:51,488
Come along, come along,
the music's already started

199
00:15:51,512 --> 00:15:52,822
in the chapel.

200
00:15:52,846 --> 00:15:55,738
We'll take care of her
or take care of her tree.

201
00:15:55,762 --> 00:15:57,405
Here's flowers Ms. Lia.

202
00:15:57,429 --> 00:15:59,280
Oh, thank you Fai Lu.

203
00:15:59,304 --> 00:16:00,863
Oh, I'm so happy.

204
00:16:00,887 --> 00:16:05,887
Ms. Lia happy leave old Fai Lu?

205
00:16:05,929 --> 00:16:07,822
No, you old darling.

206
00:16:07,846 --> 00:16:09,363
You're going to live with us always.

207
00:16:09,387 --> 00:16:10,447
Oh, come along, come along.

208
00:16:10,471 --> 00:16:11,822
Don't be so sentimental.

209
00:16:11,846 --> 00:16:14,804
A wedding's no place for
sentiment, come along, come along.

210
00:16:19,221 --> 00:16:22,304
Oh girls, do be careful with that train.

211
00:16:28,721 --> 00:16:31,947
Lia my dear, what's the matter?

212
00:16:31,971 --> 00:16:33,030
I don't know.

213
00:16:33,054 --> 00:16:35,596
I feel just as I used to when...

214
00:16:37,722 --> 00:16:39,238
It's the wedding excitement.

215
00:16:39,262 --> 00:16:40,971
No wonder the child's upset.

216
00:16:43,054 --> 00:16:45,804
Don't worry, I'm all right now.

217
00:16:52,762 --> 00:16:54,637
Now everybody, be calm, be calm.

218
00:16:56,054 --> 00:16:58,363
Don't get excited.

219
00:16:58,387 --> 00:17:00,304
Watch me, see how calm I am.

220
00:17:03,054 --> 00:17:04,197
They're ready.

221
00:17:04,221 --> 00:17:05,405
Now, be perfectly calm.

222
00:17:05,429 --> 00:17:06,364
Be perfectly calm, Doctor.

223
00:17:06,388 --> 00:17:07,947
Remember, I'll be there with you.

224
00:17:07,971 --> 00:17:11,280
Now, quick, we go in by the side door.

225
00:17:11,304 --> 00:17:14,863
Ready, ring, right hand,
left hand, pass over.

226
00:17:14,887 --> 00:17:16,780
Pass over, pass over, pass over.

227
00:17:16,804 --> 00:17:18,655
Ring, right hand.

228
00:18:25,012 --> 00:18:28,197
We are gathered together
here in the sight of God

229
00:18:28,221 --> 00:18:30,179
and in the face of this congregation

230
00:18:31,221 --> 00:18:34,137
to join together this man and this woman

231
00:18:35,762 --> 00:18:40,012
in holy matrimony, which
is an honorable estate in-

232
00:18:44,179 --> 00:18:45,762
Ms. Lia, Ms. Lia.

233
00:18:49,721 --> 00:18:50,573
Doctor.

234
00:18:50,597 --> 00:18:52,846
Ms. Lia, Fu Manchu alive.

235
00:18:58,804 --> 00:19:00,304
Fu Manchu alive.

236
00:19:02,096 --> 00:19:03,655
Oh, I knew it.

237
00:19:03,679 --> 00:19:05,363
I felt him near me.

238
00:19:05,387 --> 00:19:06,738
She's dead.

239
00:19:21,387 --> 00:19:23,679
Now please don't cry anymore, dear.

240
00:19:27,721 --> 00:19:29,238
Did you find anything, Smith?

241
00:19:29,262 --> 00:19:30,262
Not a thing.

242
00:19:31,096 --> 00:19:34,137
Some agent of Fu Manchu
is responsible for this.

243
00:19:34,971 --> 00:19:37,429
I think it is Fu Manchu himself.

244
00:19:39,012 --> 00:19:41,447
But I saw Fu Manchu dead.

245
00:19:41,471 --> 00:19:43,113
I pronounced him dead.

246
00:19:43,137 --> 00:19:45,221
Yes, and I saw him sealed in his coffin.

247
00:19:46,429 --> 00:19:50,447
But I'm convinced now that he lives.

248
00:19:50,471 --> 00:19:53,905
Wasn't there an autopsy
performed on the body?

249
00:19:53,929 --> 00:19:56,863
No, out of respect for his religion.

250
00:19:56,887 --> 00:19:57,887
Stupid.

251
00:19:58,846 --> 00:20:01,863
I deserve any criticism
you might care to make,

252
00:20:01,887 --> 00:20:03,113
lady Agatha.

253
00:20:03,137 --> 00:20:04,613
Nonsense.

254
00:20:04,637 --> 00:20:06,322
It was on my pronouncement
that you pass the body.

255
00:20:06,346 --> 00:20:08,863
Good of you to share the blame, Petrie.

256
00:20:08,887 --> 00:20:10,887
But I'm afraid it's not gonna help much.

257
00:20:29,179 --> 00:20:31,262
But how can he still be alive?

258
00:20:32,804 --> 00:20:36,179
The poison he took was
obviously not poison.

259
00:20:37,054 --> 00:20:39,471
The funeral was conducted
entirely by Orientals.

260
00:20:40,596 --> 00:20:43,012
I don't doubt the embalming was fake.

261
00:20:44,054 --> 00:20:47,238
Anything is possible with a
man is rich and diabolical

262
00:20:47,262 --> 00:20:48,988
as Fu Manchu.

263
00:20:49,012 --> 00:20:51,554
But still I'm not
convinced that he's alive.

264
00:20:53,262 --> 00:20:56,988
I'm sure of it, I felt it.

